                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_107096">Ravenstone</placeName>.
                         
                        <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> de <surname>Basingham</surname>, lord of <placeName role="lord" type="manor" key="place_108078">Wahull</placeName>
                        </persName>,<!--<note type="foot" n="1">John inherited the estate in 1238 and died in 1239. (<hi rend="italic">V.C.H. Bucks.</hi> iv. 441.)</note>--> grants to <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> the clerk</persName> for his homage and service, a messuage near the cemetery, and 3 acres of land in <placeName key="place_107096">R<supplied>avenstone</supplied>
                        </placeName>. Rent: 3/-. 
                        Witnesses: <persName>
                           <forename>Hugh</forename> de <surname>Legh</surname>
                        </persName>,
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Ralph</forename> de <surname>Parentin</surname>
                        </persName>, 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> (?) de <surname>R[ave]nestone</surname>
                        </persName>, 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Simon</forename> of <surname>R<supplied>avenstone</supplied>
                           </surname>
                        </persName>, 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> 
                           <surname>Caperon</surname>
                        </persName>,
                        <persName nymRef="Caperon">
                           <forename>Ralph</forename> his son</persName>,
                        William son of [<gap/>]†, 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> the <surname>cook</surname>
                        </persName>. 
                        <origDate notBefore="1238" notAfter="1239" precision="low">
